mory, and local historical production played key roles in the continued proclivity of the county's population for massive carnage. In the process, the history of Macheng also provides a case study in the way events and trends of national significance in the history of China have been experienced at the local level.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362619540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626195423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626195/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles